<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-05-12a.161.5" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100574" speakername="Baroness Scotland of Asthal" colon=":" colnum="161"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds06/text/60512w02.htm#60512w02_spmin3">
	<p pid="a.161.5/1">The financial implications of amalgamating different levels of precept remain under consideration. We are presently working on transitional arrangements to allow for convergence of precepts over several years. We are committed to paying 100 per cent. of reasonable set-up revenue and capital costs of restructuring, net of reasonable savings. The projected level of these costs and savings is a matter for negotiations currently taking place.</p>
</reply>
